Drinks are on point, creative and strong. Atmosphere is very good, fun place for a date, and music is well done. Also great location, around the corner of the L train Bedford stop. The only reason I took away one star was because of how the ordering works, one person was dedicated to drinks, one for appetizers and one for food, it seemed a different person was designated for a different task, which was a little confusing and probably was the reason why some of our orders was wrong/never showed up. They took it off the bill accordingly with no fuss for the things that didn't arrive, and it was a very busy night and we were a large group, so it might have just been a one off experience in general. Still, a great place overall and would go again. Really recommend the vegetarian calamari and trying out their seasonal drinks.

The service here is impeccable. You can tell everyone loves being there or at least like what they do. I came around 8 pm on a Friday evening with reservations made. I sat in the winter garden located in the back. I started off with the Berry Manilow cocktail. I loved it so much that I kept getting them throughout the meal. I'm a sucker for a well-made cocktail so this place will have a place in my heart. We started off with the cauliflower hummus. It was good. I didn't really like the beet addition to it. It was sweet which isn't something I would like for my hummus. Then we shared the mussels and the fish. I really enjoyed the fish. The skin was nice and crispy and then the meat was tender and fresh. The mushrooms were a nice addition as well. The mussels were really good. It was cooked in a coconut curry so if you're a fan of coconut this is definitely for you.

This is your quintessential local pub - ok "gastropub" if you will.  You're more likely than not to find one of the convivial owners behind the bar, and it's easy to while away a few hours (or just that one drink after work) hanging out there. It reminds me of the Williamsburg that I used to live in, with friendly local establishments, now long gone. Or, I should say, *mostly* long gone - this one nicely recovers the mood...  Note: The "gastro"pub part isn't accidental, the food is really quite excellent too!

I arrived to the newly opened Midnights Restaurant for Saturday brunch for three people and we were seated immediately as there were not a lot of patrons.  I ordered the Hemingway Cocktail which consisted of Flor de Caña rum, lime. marischano, and grapefruit. It was pretty delicious.  For my appetizer, I ordered the Farmers Market Salad Seasonal Greens which was comprised of fruits, herbs, and flowers and it was probably the best summer salad I have ever eaten.  For my main, I ordered the Breakfast Sandwich, which was made up of duck egg, duck confit, cumin aioli, and emmentaler cheese. The sandwich was decent but not memorable.  The staff was very friendly and they were very accessible. The decor of the inside of the restaurant was classic chic and the one thing I really loved is that they have a beautiful outdoor backyard patio.
Incredible dishes from the appetizers through the desserts. The short rib was divine.

Midnights in Williamsburg is an excellent eatery, cocktail spot and laid back place to be. I love the food, the cocktails and the staff are fun to interact with. Great spot for brunch or even dinner. The menu is well thought out and delicious. Bring all your friends and enjoy the meal and booze!
